1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,360
e, Chris, abbiamo creato un clima di Pontignano dentro la Commissione europea,

2
00:00:06,980 --> 00:00:09,080
che è abbastanza un raggiungimento.

3
00:00:09,300 --> 00:00:14,000
Allora, cercherò di rispondere alla vostra questione, Chris,

4
00:00:14,860 --> 00:00:21,860
non referendo quasi a tutto al campo in cui ho cercato di essere attivo,

5
00:00:21,940 --> 00:00:24,320
ma cercherò di rispondere in termini più generali.

6
00:00:25,220 --> 00:00:27,880
Allora, se guardiamo i ultimi 10 anni,

7
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:36,240
l'Europa, che è spesso trattata di non aver messo in posto sufficienti reformi strutturali,

8
00:00:36,460 --> 00:00:37,880
e possiamo tutti sbagliare su questo,

9
00:00:38,660 --> 00:00:43,620
ha messo in posto 4 strutturali strutturali storiche di se stessa.

10
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:46,660
È molto conosciuto che, solo in 10 anni,

11
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:49,960
ci sia stato l'accedimento del mercato singolo,

12
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:54,080
del mercato singolo, dell'enlargimento e della Costituzione.

13
00:00:54,080 --> 00:00:58,840
Questo è molto conosciuto, ma è troppo facilmente dimenticato.

14
00:00:59,180 --> 00:01:02,760
E non dovremmo dimenticare che ogni esercizio di questi obiettivi

15
00:01:02,760 --> 00:01:06,500
è stato pronunciato come quasi impossibile

16
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:09,940
da molto dell'intelligenza in Europa,

17
00:01:10,260 --> 00:01:12,000
negli Stati Uniti e altrimenti,

18
00:01:12,180 --> 00:01:14,220
forse un o due anni prima,

19
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:18,940
che è passato in posto punctuale.

20
00:01:18,940 --> 00:01:24,960
Ora, credo che sia anche normalmente sbagliato

21
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:27,300
quanto queste 4 cose

22
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:32,640
possano avere una relazione con il grande problema dell'economia europea

23
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:34,540
e la sua competitività.

24
00:01:34,880 --> 00:01:37,960
E' in più di nessun dubbio che l'Europa non presta bene

25
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:40,320
dal punto di vista della competitività,

26
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:43,660
ma vorrei fare il punto che,

27
00:01:43,660 --> 00:01:46,800
è che questo possa essere in parte a causa

28
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:49,500
della concentrazione delle energie politiche

29
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:52,660
su questi 4 obiettivi,

30
00:01:53,620 --> 00:01:55,740
ma che, allo stesso tempo,

31
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:59,540
avendo trasformato l'Europa in questo modo,

32
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:00,180
per esempio,

33
00:02:00,580 --> 00:02:04,660
rendendo l'Europa un po' più simile all'U.S. come un'entità,

34
00:02:04,820 --> 00:02:08,480
può solo aiutare la crescita futuro e la competitività in Europa.

35
00:02:09,640 --> 00:02:11,140
È chiaro, per esempio,

36
00:02:11,140 --> 00:02:14,120
che la singola correnza

37
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:15,700
ha portato con la correnza

38
00:02:18,780 --> 00:02:22,060
da indisciplina fiscale a disciplina fiscale.

39
00:02:22,420 --> 00:02:24,620
È ben possibile che, nel termine sottile,

40
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:27,240
questo possa aver portato una crescita più bassa,

41
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:29,620
ma credo che tutti aggrediremmo

42
00:02:29,620 --> 00:02:33,820
che questo sia un prequisito sottile per il sviluppo futuro.

43
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:37,060
Anche la costituzione,

44
00:02:37,060 --> 00:02:40,360
solo il mercato, solo la correnza, l'enlargimento,

45
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:42,060
la costituzione, anche la costituzione.

46
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:44,560
Giuliano, che è la relazione

47
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:47,560
tra la costituzione e la competitività?

48
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:48,520
Non c'è una relazione.

49
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:52,440
Ma è chiaro a tutti

50
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:56,220
che una compagnia non può essere competitiva

51
00:02:56,220 --> 00:02:59,500
se ha un processo di decisione veloce e incerta.

52
00:03:01,260 --> 00:03:03,920
Questo non è molto diverso per la nostra nazione

53
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:05,580
o per un set di nazioni.

54
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:09,220
A livello che la costituzione

55
00:03:09,220 --> 00:03:11,840
porti un processo di decisione

56
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:13,460
più racionali e veloci,

57
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:19,480
credo che questo aiuterà la competitività d'Europa.

58
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:22,580
Quindi, quando vedremo

59
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:27,140
i ultimi 10 anni della storia europea,

60
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:30,660
credo che confermerà che l'Europa

61
00:03:30,660 --> 00:03:33,680
non ha fatto abbastanza bene

62
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:35,780
dal punto di vista della performance economica,

63
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:39,220
ma probabilmente abbastanza la base

64
00:03:39,220 --> 00:03:42,080
per una performance economica più soddisfatto

65
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:44,060
dal punto di vista dell'Europa.

66
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:46,900
È chiaro, però,

67
00:03:47,260 --> 00:03:49,920
che non possiamo solo restare là

68
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:51,940
e aspettare questa struttura fondamentale

69
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:54,360
di trasformazione per portare a livello

70
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:56,580
la dividenza in termini di crescita più alta

71
00:03:56,580 --> 00:03:59,100
e dell'implicamento e della competitività.

72
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:02,340
Ci sono le politiche necessarie.

73
00:04:03,180 --> 00:04:04,480
E qui, Chris,

74
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,860
per rispondere alla vostra domanda

75
00:04:06,860 --> 00:04:08,700
o al titolo di questa sessione,

76
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,580
i successi e i setbacki in Europa

77
00:04:10,580 --> 00:04:11,720
over the past 10 years,

78
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:14,700
what I would regard as a major problem

79
00:04:14,700 --> 00:04:16,980
which has emerged more and more clearly

80
00:04:16,980 --> 00:04:19,520
is a decoupling.

81
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:22,440
A decoupling by member state

82
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:24,000
between two things.

83
00:04:24,740 --> 00:04:27,380
The willingness to accept

84
00:04:27,380 --> 00:04:30,680
a somewhat greater integration and coordination

85
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:32,540
Europe-wise,

86
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:36,760
selectively, without exceeding,

87
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:39,160
with greater attention paid at the same time

88
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:40,580
also to subsidiarity,

89
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:43,240
but to accept some greater coordination

90
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:46,180
in certain area, one prerequisite,

91
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:49,020
and the other one to be serious and tough

92
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:51,480
in terms of domestic economic reforms.

93
00:04:52,340 --> 00:04:55,000
To simplify things exceedingly,

94
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:57,660
I believe that we have seen

95
00:04:57,660 --> 00:04:59,760
an increasing decoupling in Europe

96
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:02,460
between these two necessary prerequisites,

97
00:05:02,460 --> 00:05:03,160
in my view,

98
00:05:03,620 --> 00:05:06,020
in order to have a competitive Europe,

99
00:05:06,220 --> 00:05:09,160
not just an internal competition

100
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,540
between one and the other.

101
00:05:11,060 --> 00:05:12,160
To simplify things,

102
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:14,920
and at the risk of being unjust,

103
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:18,180
certainly Germany and France

104
00:05:18,180 --> 00:05:20,380
have once again displayed

105
00:05:20,380 --> 00:05:23,240
a greater willingness to accept coordination,

106
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:26,180
including in the constitutional debate,

107
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:29,740
than, say, the UK or Spain.

108
00:05:30,140 --> 00:05:31,700
At the same time, there have been

109
00:05:31,700 --> 00:05:33,460
pretty recalcitrant in terms of

110
00:05:33,460 --> 00:05:34,880
domestic economic reforms.

111
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,540
I believe we need both things

112
00:05:37,540 --> 00:05:39,220
if we want a competitive Europe,

113
00:05:39,340 --> 00:05:41,400
but there has been this increasingly

114
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,680
visible decoupling.

115
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:45,300
Now, I think we should ask ourselves

116
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:48,220
the question, is there an inherent conflict

117
00:05:48,220 --> 00:05:50,180
between these two attitudes,

118
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:51,860
both of which, in my view,

119
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:53,800
are necessary for a competitive Europe?

120
00:05:54,260 --> 00:05:56,960
I believe there is not inherent conflict.

121
00:05:57,780 --> 00:05:59,440
Of course, as I said,

122
00:06:00,020 --> 00:06:01,280
a great deal of attention,

123
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:03,960
and here we can only learn from the UK,

124
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:05,880
has to be paid to subsidiarity.

125
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:08,300
And in certain areas,

126
00:06:08,540 --> 00:06:10,500
we have in the last ten years

127
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,860
brought about greater coordination,

128
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:17,160
but some devolution to the national authorities.

129
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:19,120
I can here mention perhaps

130
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,720
the reform in the area of competition.

131
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:22,740
But I don't see that

132
00:06:22,740 --> 00:06:24,200
there is an inherent conflict

133
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:25,800
between these two attitudes.

134
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:28,040
And I must say, Italy, for one,

135
00:06:28,140 --> 00:06:29,420
as I see it,

136
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:32,680
has been rather more close

137
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,880
to Germany and France

138
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:35,240
in terms of acceptance

139
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:37,220
of a greater degree of coordination,

140
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:39,140
and, at least in principle,

141
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:41,860
but also with some implementations

142
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:45,340
ready towards economic reforms domestically.

143
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:47,000
Now, in this context,

144
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,900
I see a very substantial hope

145
00:06:49,900 --> 00:06:52,280
in the enlargement.

146
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:53,600
We normally consider

147
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:55,780
the effects of enlargement

148
00:06:55,780 --> 00:06:57,820
at constant policies.

149
00:06:58,260 --> 00:06:59,540
Enlargement will not

150
00:06:59,540 --> 00:07:01,360
keep policies constant.

151
00:07:01,620 --> 00:07:03,300
Enlargement will transform

152
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:05,980
the policy trade-offs, I believe.

153
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,600
And what I see

154
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:08,780
in the new member states,

155
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:10,280
most of them, all of them,

156
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,520
is at the same time the willingness

157
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:14,040
to have greater coordination

158
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,980
and, for sure, a strong

159
00:07:15,980 --> 00:07:18,180
central enforcer of the rule

160
00:07:18,180 --> 00:07:19,260
of the European Commission

161
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:21,920
and a tough policy of domestic

162
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:22,940
economic reform.

163
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:25,960
And here, again, to make one

164
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:27,460
reference to Italy,

165
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:29,600
with all the abstraction

166
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,580
of these geometrical discussions

167
00:07:31,580 --> 00:07:33,140
about foreign politics,

168
00:07:33,780 --> 00:07:36,020
I believe that a country like Italy,

169
00:07:36,420 --> 00:07:38,020
with a government like the present

170
00:07:38,020 --> 00:07:39,020
government of Italy,

171
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:41,520
should perhaps even intensify

172
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:43,900
the efforts to become a reference point

173
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:45,680
without discarding

174
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:47,820
other friendships and alliances

175
00:07:47,820 --> 00:07:49,920
for this group

176
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,760
of small

177
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:53,720
and or new

178
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:55,720
member states, which are really

179
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:58,600
rejuvenating the European Union.

180
00:08:02,380 --> 00:08:04,060
My time is almost over.

181
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:05,800
One

182
00:08:07,340 --> 00:08:07,820
important

183
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:09,720
setback

184
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:11,900
or insufficient progress

185
00:08:11,900 --> 00:08:13,720
is the explanation

186
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:15,940
of Europe to Europe's citizens,

187
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:17,800
in particular

188
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,240
to the younger generations.

189
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,780
And here I see,

190
00:08:21,780 --> 00:08:24,020
frankly, a monumental paradox.

191
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,000
Why?

192
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:27,440
We all know that the younger generations

193
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:29,920
lose interest and love

194
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:31,660
for Europe, especially because

195
00:08:31,660 --> 00:08:33,920
they have not lived through the things

196
00:08:33,920 --> 00:08:36,100
that Europe has been able to remove.

197
00:08:37,220 --> 00:08:38,220
And at the same

198
00:08:38,220 --> 00:08:40,300
time, if we think of it, Europe

199
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:42,260
is the key ally

200
00:08:42,260 --> 00:08:44,400
of the future generations.

201
00:08:44,740 --> 00:08:46,340
Giuliano referred to

202
00:08:46,340 --> 00:08:48,460
the dimension of the future, as I

203
00:08:48,460 --> 00:08:49,320
see it.

204
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:52,520
Europe is the main driver,

205
00:08:52,780 --> 00:08:54,300
the main introducer

206
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:56,140
of a reference to the future

207
00:08:56,140 --> 00:08:58,440
in our societies and in our debates,

208
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:00,380
both in terms of

209
00:09:00,380 --> 00:09:02,320
forcing us all to consider

210
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:04,480
the future and in terms

211
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:06,260
of forcing

212
00:09:06,260 --> 00:09:07,980
us to respect the future,

213
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:10,300
consider the future. What would have

214
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:12,740
been in each of our countries

215
00:09:12,740 --> 00:09:14,440
the policies, the

216
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:16,440
politics, if we had not

217
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:18,340
had the target of 1993

218
00:09:18,860 --> 00:09:20,040
for the single market,

219
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:22,540
of 1997, to bring down

220
00:09:22,540 --> 00:09:23,140
the deficit?

221
00:09:24,260 --> 00:09:26,280
Now Lisbon is a bit weak because it

222
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,560
does not crucify

223
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:30,140
countries similarly

224
00:09:30,140 --> 00:09:31,540
effectively to that.

225
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:34,260
So if there has been a reference to the

226
00:09:34,260 --> 00:09:36,380
future, it has been most of the times

227
00:09:36,380 --> 00:09:38,460
brought by what the collective

228
00:09:38,460 --> 00:09:40,460
wisdom of member states and the commission

229
00:09:40,460 --> 00:09:42,680
have decided

230
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:44,220
should be a future

231
00:09:44,220 --> 00:09:45,620
reference for Europe.

232
00:09:46,220 --> 00:09:48,000
And it has forced

233
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:50,220
countries and societies to

234
00:09:50,220 --> 00:09:51,400
respect the future.

235
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:53,700
And really,

236
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:55,860
many of our countries

237
00:09:55,860 --> 00:09:58,400
were running with

238
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:00,200
a beatitude of

239
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:02,340
unawareness, deficits of

240
00:10:02,340 --> 00:10:04,220
12-15% of GDP

241
00:10:04,220 --> 00:10:06,300
without there being any debate.

242
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:08,360
This was so at the beginning

243
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:10,040
of the last ten years, Chris.

244
00:10:10,420 --> 00:10:12,340
Now we make

245
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:14,200
fights

246
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,540
about whether it is 2.9

247
00:10:16,540 --> 00:10:17,680
or 3.1.

248
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:20,400
But the substantial effect of

249
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:22,660
Europe is that it has forced

250
00:10:22,660 --> 00:10:24,260
upon domestic political

251
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:26,560
processes the respect for our

252
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:28,340
children, for the future

253
00:10:28,340 --> 00:10:30,460
generations, not to have

254
00:10:30,460 --> 00:10:32,540
them born with the burden

255
00:10:32,540 --> 00:10:35,200
on their shoulders of the public debt.

256
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:36,540
So I think

257
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:38,500
that it should be possible, and

258
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:40,600
I'm delighted that President Barroso

259
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:42,600
has assigned a special responsibility

260
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,440
to Vice President Marco

261
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:46,540
Wallstrom to make an effort to

262
00:10:46,540 --> 00:10:48,780
explain Europe. I think that those

263
00:10:48,780 --> 00:10:50,540
to whom we find

264
00:10:50,540 --> 00:10:52,600
it most difficult to transfer

265
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,440
the message of Europe, that is

266
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:56,740
the younger generations, are really those

267
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:58,440
which we should be able to

268
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:00,420
mobilize. Final note,

269
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,380
I think in ten years

270
00:11:02,380 --> 00:11:04,720
the relevance of the commission

271
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:06,100
for all its weaknesses

272
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:08,880
has increased.

273
00:11:09,380 --> 00:11:10,720
May I conclude with

274
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:11,820
a personal

275
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:14,500
reference here. Ten years

276
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:15,960
ago, believe it or not,

277
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:18,680
when I was first appointed to Brussels,

278
